dismissalComment.html: and he strikes first ball! Is he the one-day Graeme Swann? First ball of his spell, Pollard hits a length and as the ball angles across Ponting opens the face and runs it off the face to a tumbling Ramdin who holds on to a neat catch

Gayle remains Bollinger's bunny, what an over this has been, Gayle opens  the face, gets a bit of an outside edge towards short cover, Clarke latches on to an overhead catch there, Bollinger has two, that's the fourth time he has dismissed Gayle

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Smith run out (Clarke) 21 (21b 2x4 1x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: short of a length on off stump, Simmons goes back and across and pushes to cover, takes a step forward, then hesitates, at the other end Smith sets off but gets shooed back and that does him in as Clarke nails a direct hit, superbly fielded there in the covers and West Indies lose their sixth

dismissalComment.html: smacked but straight to Clarke at cover! Bollinger drags it short as Simmons goes to the leg side, looking to smack it down the ground, and the result is a flat-batted slap into the vice-captain's lap, that was hit hard and should leave a sting, but well held

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin lbw b Smith 3 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: plumb and Smith has his first ODI wicket! Tossed up, pitches in line with the sticks and straightens a touch, the sidespin does the trick as Ramdin plays for turn and is hit in front and the Australians rush to congratulate a red-faced Smith

dismissalText.commentary: Ravi Rampaul st Haddin b Smith 4 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: stumped and it's all over! Rampaul thows his bat at the one that drifts away, dragging his back leg marginally forward, Haddin collects and breaks the sticks, yelling out a relieved "THANK YOU" as he does so, and replays show Rampaul's foot was on the line so that is the end of that

dismissalText.commentary: Ravi Rampaul st Haddin b Smith 4 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

commentTextItems.html: stumped and it's all over! Rampaul thows his bat at the one that drifts away, dragging his back leg marginally forward, Haddin collects and breaks the sticks, yelling out a relieved "THANK YOU" as he does so, and replays show Rampaul's foot was on the line so that is the end of that

commentPostTextItems.html: End of the ODI series and its 4-0 to Australia. Smith gets his second. The players head off and shake hands with the opposition. We have two Twenty20s to go, the first of which is on February 21 in Hobart. We will have the action live for you. Ponting is the Man of the Series for his 293 runs at 73.75. Bye!

commentTextItems.html: comes out but cannot connect on the loopy delivery, wasn't to the pitch and ends up pushing it down the ground for a single
out comes the slog sweep which gets him a single
fuller and wider and now he slashes over the covers, but Sammy sends him back after they run two
no turn, pretty short, and Rampaul goes back to block
too short so Sammy deposits that over mid-on's head for four

commentTextItems.html: hits a good length, Sammy pushes at it uneasily outside off
hits a length and moves away, Rampaul is squared up and edges to point, Ponting collects and hits the stumps and Rampaul gets an overthrow
gets over it and pushes it away again
gets back and pushes at the ball, point runs in

dismissalText.commentary: Nikita Miller c Clarke b McKay 22 (20b 1x4 0x6) SR: 110

commentTextItems.html: end of a frustrating stand as Miller is forced up by a short ball and slaps it to Clarke at cover, he stands there for a while thinking the ball was too high, but no reaction from the umpires and West Indies lose their ninth

commentPostTextItems.html: Stubborn rearguard from Miller comes to an end. He has reason to feel aggrieved because replays show that ball was pretty high. Here's Rampaul.

commentTextItems.html: gets back and pushes the ball away

headshotImage.caption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: dropped in the deep! Sammy pulls a half-tracker over midwicket, out to where David Hussey runs across a long way and dives but cannot hold on
another flowing shot from Sammy against Smith, skipping out and hitting straight through the line, dumping that over cow corner for the biggest six of the day
again too short and Sammy punches it to extra cover
short and flat, Miller chops it into the covers for one more
flighted on the stumps, Sammy takes it off the front pad for one
shorter ball and pulls uneasily down to long leg with an edge

commentPostTextItems.html: Drinks on the field. Mandatory ball change after this interval.

commentTextItems.html: nicely driven on the rise over extra cover, freeing the arms, good shot
gets nice and tall and pushes the ball to point

headshotImage.longCaption: Narsingh Deonarine player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Michael Clarke c Deonarine b Rampaul 47 (58b 0x4 1x6) SR: 81.03

dismissalComment.html: well there's an easy dismissal, but it looked tense for a few seconds! Rampaul digs it in, Clarke gets up to ride the bounce and turn the ball past midwicket but gets a leading edge that balloons up toward mid-on, Hinds runs in from the other side but its Deonarine from short midwicket who calls for it and takes it as he tumbles over with Hinds staring

dismissalText.commentary: Cameron White c Ramdin b Rampaul 22 (33b 1x4 0x6) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: fourth short ball in a row, down the leg side, White is late on the pull and the ball kisses his gloves through to Ramdin who moves across to his left and holds on

headshotImage.caption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle c Clarke b Bollinger 14 (5b 0x4 2x6) SR: 280

dismissalComment.html: Gayle remains Bollinger's bunny, what an over this has been, Gayle opens  the face, gets a bit of an outside edge towards short cover, Clarke latches on to an overhead catch there, Bollinger has two, that's the fourth time he has dismissed Gayle

headshotImage.longCaption: James Hopes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Kieron Pollard c Smith b Hopes 45 (51b 4x4 2x6) SR: 88.23

dismissalComment.html: nice catch there Smith! Hopes tries the short ball again, Pollard obliges with a much squarer pull shot, not as controlled at the previous one, and a running Smith takes it at deep backward square leg

headshotImage.caption: Wavell Hinds player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Wavell Hinds player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Wavell Hinds player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Wavell Hinds c Smith b Harris 5 (13b 0x4 0x6) SR: 38.46

dismissalComment.html: there's a catch to the rookie! Short ball comes onto Hinds quicker than he probably anticipates and he's all at sea trying to pull and Smith runs across from square leg, calling for it, and takes it in front of midwicket

headshotImage.caption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons c Clarke b Bollinger 29 (44b 4x4 0x6) SR: 65.9

dismissalComment.html: smacked but straight to Clarke at cover! Bollinger drags it short as Simmons goes to the leg side, looking to smack it down the ground, and the result is a flat-batted slap into the vice-captain's lap, that was hit hard and should leave a sting, but well held

headshotImage.caption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Smith run out (Clarke) 21 (21b 2x4 1x6) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: short of a length on off stump, Simmons goes back and across and pushes to cover, takes a step forward, then hesitates, at the other end Smith sets off but gets shooed back and that does him in as Clarke nails a direct hit, superbly fielded there in the covers and West Indies lose their sixth

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin lbw b Smith 3 (4b 0x4 0x6) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: plumb and Smith has his first ODI wicket! Tossed up, pitches in line with the sticks and straightens a touch, the sidespin does the trick as Ramdin plays for turn and is hit in front and the Australians rush to congratulate a red-faced Smith

dismissalText.commentary: Daren Sammy not out 47 (41b 3x4 3x6) SR: 114.63

headshotImage.caption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Nikita Miller c Clarke b McKay 22 (20b 1x4 0x6) SR: 110

dismissalComment.html: end of a frustrating stand as Miller is forced up by a short ball and slaps it to Clarke at cover, he stands there for a while thinking the ball was too high, but no reaction from the umpires and West Indies lose their ninth

dismissalText.commentary: Ravi Rampaul st Haddin b Smith 4 (7b 0x4 0x6) SR: 57.14

dismissalComment.html: stumped and it's all over! Rampaul thows his bat at the one that drifts away, dragging his back leg marginally forward, Haddin collects and breaks the sticks, yelling out a relieved "THANK YOU" as he does so, and replays show Rampaul's foot was on the line so that is the end of that
